summary: Congress is actively considering banning TikTok in the United States due to concerns about its potential ties to the Chinese government and its access to sensitive user data. While the bill faces an uncertain fate in the Senate, recent votes suggest an increased likelihood of passage. However, experts caution that even if a ban is enacted, it could take time to implement and may face legal challenges. summary: Tesla has announced price reductions across various models in the United States, including the Model Y, Model X, and Model S. The Model Y, in particular, has witnessed a drop to its lowest price ever. The price cuts align with Tesla's recent strategy shift, which includes reducing the cost of its vehicles and expanding its FSD offerings. name: Carolina Hurricanes
summary: The Carolina Hurricanes are set to begin their NHL playoff journey, taking on the New York Islanders in the first round. The series, which begins in Raleigh, will feature a matchup between two teams with strong goaltending and scoring depth. Hurricanes coach Rod Brind'Amour has been building towards this moment, aiming to establish a perennial contender in Carolina, and the team will face a tough test in the Islanders, who are making their first playoff appearance since 2022. Canes fans can catch the action on TV, streaming platforms, or at PNC Arena, where the team will aim to earn a Game 1 victory. The projected lineup for the Hurricanes includes Frederik Andersen as starting goaltender, Seth Jarvis at left wing, Martin Necas at center, and Andrei Svechnikov at right wing on the top line, while the Islanders will counter with Ilya Sorokin in net.

name: Cybertruck recall
summary: Tesla has announced a major recall of its Cybertruck electric pickup truck, affecting nearly 4,000 vehicles. The recall is due to a faulty accelerator pedal that can stick, potentially causing unintended acceleration. This marks Tesla's largest recall in several years and comes at a challenging time for CEO Elon Musk, who is facing scrutiny over Twitter's handling of misinformation and other issues. The Cybertruck has been delayed several times and is now expected to enter production in 2023. The accelerator pedal issue has added to the truck's woes, with Tesla announcing a fix involving the installation of rivets. The recall is a setback for Tesla and may further dent its reputation for quality control.

summary: The FA Cup, one of the oldest football competitions in the world, will undergo significant changes next season. Replays after drawn matches will be eliminated, and the final will take place on the penultimate weekend of the season. This is a major departure from the traditional format, which had included replays since the competition's inception in 1871. The changes are intended to reduce fixture congestion and ease player workload, especially during the later stages of the tournament.
